THE HIDDEN TRUTH
The best candidates often don't apply.
They get found.
Their LinkedIn profile does the work. Recruiters reach them through search
because they are visible, specific, and unmistakably searchable. That is now
the most important job a profile does.

You're being scraped, scored, and ranked by AI.
These platforms continuously crawl LinkedIn, Github, and public profiles — building candidate
files before any job is posted. If your keywords don't match their filters, you never surface.
