LINKEDIN SHOWS YOU TO THE RECRUITER
BEFORE THE BOOLEAN SEARCH
Sometimes the recruiter
doesn't search at all.
When a recruiter posts a job, LinkedIn hands them a stack of matching candidates before any search happens. Your profile is
either in that stack, or it isn't.
The three signals it runs on.
What the job needs
The required skills, title, and location feed straight
into the algorithm. If your profile uses different
words, you don't get matched.
Whether you're open
Turn on Open to Work in private mode (recruiters
only, hidden from your boss). It moves you to the
top of the stack instantly.
Who the recruiter likes
Every candidate they save or message teaches
the algorithm their taste. You want to be one of
the ones they save.
35%
Higher inMail acceptance from candidates the algorithm surfaces vs. candidates found by boolean search alone.
