A searchable profile gets you
found. Smart engagement gets
you remember.
40x
More opportunities land in complete profiles vs.
incomplete ones — LinkedIn’s algorithm promotes
profile completeness in search.
3.2x
More profile views for members with 500+ connections
vs. fewer than 100. Network size is a ranking signal.
LinkedIn Data, 2023
5+
Thoughtful comments on others’ posts per day signal
you as “active” to the algorithm — driving more
visibility than any content you post.
The job seeker's playbook
Comment before you post. Drop 5 substantive comments
on posts by hiring managers, recruiters, and people in your
target — every weekday.
Post 2-3x per week, not daily. Share a lesson, a framework,
or a case study from your experience. Under 1,500
characters. Line breaks matter.
Lead with a hook. The first line is all most people see. Make
it specific — a number, a question, or a contradiction.
Reply to every comment in the first hour. Early comment
velocity is the single biggest reach lever the algorithm watches.
Grow to 500+ connections deliberately. Connect with
people in your target role, industry, and target
companies — not just everyone.
Sources: LinkedIn Data, 2023 (Global): Richard van der Blom. “5 LinkedIn
Engagement Signals That Predict Algorithm Reach.” 2023, SocialInsider Benchmark
Report, 2023.
